:<font size="15">יאשׁיּהוּ</font></div>

===Pronunciation===
יאשׁיּהוּ  -  יאשׁיּה / yô'shîyâh  yô'shîyâhû / yo-she-yaw', yo-she-yaw'-hoo

===Etymology===
From the same root as [[אשׁוּיה]] {{HH|803}} and [[יהּ]] {{HH|3050}}; founded of Jah; 

===Proper noun===
'''יאשׁיּהוּ'''

# Joshijah, the name of two Israelites: - [[Josiah]].

